The '''''Ranger''''' was a [[Centax-class heavy frigate|''Centax''-class heavy frigate]] used by the [[Republic Navy/Legends|Republic Navy]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. It was [[Jedi General/Legends|Jedi General]] [[Nejaa Halcyon]]'s [[Command ship/Legends|command ship]] during the [[Battle of Praesitlyn]]. It was commanded by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Quegh]]. Other crew included [[Ensign/Legends|Ensign]] [[Dejock]], [[Corporal/Legends|Corporal]] [[Ram Raders]], and [[Private/Legends|Private]] [[Slane Vick]]. In addition to its complement of [[Laser cannon/Legends|laser cannons]], the ''Ranger'' was armed with at least one secondary weapon system: a battery of two [[MG1-A proton torpedo]] tubes, fresh from development.

The ''Ranger'' fired the opening shot of the battle for [[Praesitlyn/Legends|Praesitlyn]] when it unleashed a salvo of unguided MG1-A torpedoes, removing a [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] [[Warship/Legends|warship]] from the fight. During the battle, it was boarded by [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] deployed from a [[skirmisher ship]] which had attached to its hull. Over one hundred crewmembers were killed, including the medical staff and many engineers, but Halcyon managed to drive the droids off, saving the ship and remaining crew. However, since the damage to the ''Ranger'' rendered it unable to participate further in the battle, it was scuttled.

